I '''Juan Evo Morales Ayma''' (mibait Octubre 26, 1959), a sikat king lagyung '''Evo''' ({{IPA-es|ˈeβo}}), metung yang pulitiku ampong aktibistang [[Bolivia]]n, a magsilbi antimong [[Pamuntuk ning Bolivia]], pusisyun a tatalnan na manibat kanitang 2006. Pekapun ne mu naman ning [[Pangimut para king Sosyalismu – Kasangkapang Pampulitika para king Katimawan da reng Lahi |Pangimut para king Sosyalismu]] Movement for Socialism – Political Instrument for the Sovereignty of the Peoples (MAS) ampo ing unyong ''[[Cocalero]]''. King kayang pulitika, metung yang pekapun a sosyalista, at ing pundasyun ning kayang pangapamuntuk (''presidency'') ya pin ing pamanutuk king pangapalyari king pangsa da reng bayung polisiya, ing ing pamipakilala ning metung a bayung punbatas o konstitusyon, reporma king gabun, ing pamanalis da reng miayaliwang manimunang industria king upaya ning kapamahalan, ing pamaglaban king papil ning Estados Unidos king pulitika ning bangsa, ampo ing pamagbawas king kakalulwan.<ref>http://www.commondreams.org/view/2012/03/21-6</ref>

Mibait ya king uring talapagobrang pamilyang [[Lahing Aymara|Aymara]] king Isallawi, [[Orinoca Canton]], at meragul ya i Evo a sasaup kareng kayang pengari anting metung a ortelanu. E miyari king sekundarya o high school. Migsane ya i Morales king militar lalam ning sapilitang pamagsilbing militar kilub ning pabanwa anggang 1978, at mibalik ya king propesyon ning kayang pamilya, ing pamanasik, at minalis ya kayabe ra king [[Chapare Lalawigan]]. Miras ya king pamananam [[coca]], at megi yang aktibu king unyon da reng talatanam coca, ing pangimut a ''cocalero''. Megi yang pikabalwan a aktibista kareng [[Unique Confederation of Rural Laborers of Bolivia|campesino]] (talapagobra king baryu), at mekilala ya king pamanibala king pamaglaban king tangka ning Estados Unidos a patuknangan ing pamagpatubung coca para king pamangawang cocaine antimong dake ning karelang mas maleparan a "[[Gera kareng Droga]] (''War on Drugs''). 

Miras king larangan ning pulitika ing kayang aktibismu. Megi yang pekapun ning MAS, at kapamilatan na niti, miabe ya kareng protesta sosyal antimo ing [[Laban king gas a Bolivian|laban king gas]] ampo deng [[Protesta king Cochabamba ning 2000]]. Parasan ning MAS ing mamye karagdagang upaya kareng komunidad a katutubu ampong pakakalulu ning bangsa kapamilatan ning reporma king gabun ampong pamirake ning pibandyan king gas, at bagya-bagyang meragul ing suporta na kareng alalan. 

Miyalal yang Pamuntuk ning Bolivia i Morales anyang Diciembre 18, 2005, kapamilatan ning 53.7% ning botu. Kaybat da reng adwa ampong kapitnang banwa, meragul yang mayap ing kayang mayoria; king recall referendum anyang Agosto 14, 2008, maygit adwang katlu da reng botanti ing migbotung mandatila/manatili ya king pusisyun.<ref>[http://www.democracynow.org/2008/8/12/bolivian_president_evo_morales_wins_critical Bolivian President Evo Morales Wins Critical Referendum on His Presidency], ''Democracy Now!'', August 12, 2008</ref><ref>Zaa Nkweta, [http://www.coha.org/morales-wins-referendum-but-opposition-hits-back/ Morales wins referendum but opposition hits back], ''Council on Hemispheric Affairs'', 26 Aug 2008</ref> Sinambut ne naman i Morales king alalang pang-pamuntuk anyang Diciembre 2009 kapamilatan ning 63% ning botu, at sindu na ing kayang kadwang terminu antimong pamuntuk.<ref>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2009/dec/07/morales-presidential-victory Guardian.co.uk - Evo Morales wins landslide victory in Bolivian presidential elections] Retrieved on 18 December 2009</ref>

Kritiku ne ning polisiya nang panglual ning Estados Unidos ampo ing papil da reng kumpanyang 
transnational king Latin America, at metung yang masikan a ka-alyadu da reng kapamahalan a sosyalista nang [[Hugo Chávez]] king Venezuela ampong [[Fidel Castro]] king Cuba. Anyang  Octubre 2009, mepili yang "Pangyatung Bayani ning Indung Yatu" ("World Hero of Mother Earth") i Morales king [[Pangkabilugang Kapulungan da reng Misasanmetung a Bangsa]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.laht.com/article.asp?ArticleId=342574&CategoryId=14919 | work=Latin American Herald Tribune | title=Morales Named "World Hero of Mother Earth" by UN General Assembly | accessdate=November 15, 2010}}</ref>

